ing collaborators for their middle management, supervising and operating positions. - We realized we kept on complaining about the poor general level of education and about the various gaps of Public Education systems. We also kept on complaining about how capitalism was not meritocratic enough and was leaving millions of people behind. That is why we have decided to work on it, instead of passively despising things. -  - Now think about it! What if companies could actually become the central actors of human development? What if the fine use of cutting edge neuro-sciences could be leveraged by the power of artificial intelligence to benefit millions of people?  - What if CHANCE could reveal the invisible talents of candidates to themselves and to the world of work, on a scale never heard of before? -  - And what if we told you that we were a group of 35 driven people from 9 different countries, including ex start-up founders, neuroscience and psychology experts, data scientists, software developers, HR specialists, social workers, former civil servants, artists and designers, based in Rio de Janeiro and Paris, energetically tackling this challenge heartfully? -  - Under the guidance of our Honorary Chairman, Nobel Peace Prize Laureate Pr. Muhammad Yunus, Chance team (including its NGO arm Y Generation Education) is working from two offices in Rio de Janeiro and Paris, and has already gained the technical and financial support of several international organizations in particular through international prizes from Google.org and UC Berkeley. We are also benefiting from the financial support of the French Government, through its Public Investment Bank.  Our current visionary corporate partners with whom we are working hand in hand on a daily basis are Casino Group (Franprix & Grupo Pao de Acucar), Accor Hotels (Ibis Hotels), Edenred (Ticket Restaurant), Renault etc, both in Brazil and in France. -  - We are constantly recruiting for most of our departments and are looki